        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(gateway): normalize malformed paired access lists",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #90654.\n\nMalformed persisted paired-device role or scope arrays could throw during a gateway connect upgrade check, closing the WebSocket before the client received a structured pairing response.\n\nThis change:\n\n- normalizes paired access scopes once before gateway authorization, audit logging, and pairing error details\n- normalizes existing role and scope arrays when pairing approval state is updated\n- adds real gateway-connect and persisted-state regression coverage\n- removes the permanent one-off reproduction scripts from the PR\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Gateway connect no longer crashes when persisted paired-device access arrays contain non-string entries.\n\nReal environment tested: Linux x64 Blacksmith Testbox through Crabbox, Node 24, real `startGatewayServer`, real WebSocket client, token authentication.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Started the gateway with malformed persisted `roles`, `scopes`, and `approvedScopes`, then requested an `operator.admin` scope upgrade over WebSocket.\n\nEvidence after fix: Terminal output from the real WebSocket run:\n\n```text\nConnect response: ok=false code=NOT_PAIRED reason=scope-upgrade\napprovedRoles=[\"operator\"]\napprovedScopes=[\"operator.read\"]\nPR92178_RESULT ok=false reason=scope-upgrade handshake=structured\n[ws] close: 1008 pairing required: device is asking for more scopes than currently approved\nPASS: Gateway WebSocket handshake did not crash with malformed pairing state.\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The gateway returned a structured scope-upgrade pairing response with normalized approved roles/scopes instead of throwing on `.trim()`.\n\nWhat was not tested: TLS termination and multi-hop proxying; the failing logic is inside the authenticated connect handler and was exercised over loopback WebSocket.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/server.auth.control-ui.test.ts src/infra/device-pairing.test.ts src/gateway/server/ws-connection/message-handler.post-connect-health.test.ts` — 190 tests passed after the final rebase\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/gateway/server.auth.control-ui.suite.ts src/gateway/server/ws-connection/message-handler.ts src/infra/device-pairing.ts src/infra/device-pairing.test.ts` — clean\n- `oxfmt --check` and `git diff --check` — clean\n- Testbox-through-Crabbox `pnpm check:changed` — clean on the same four-file patch content (`tbx_01kv7abqva1n7jh9kdvs19hsmb`)\n- Autoreview of `origin/main...HEAD` — clean, no accepted/actionable findings\n",
        "branch": "fix/90654-gateway-handshake-trim-crash",
